{"title":"LH Pediatrico","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/General/LH Pediatrico iPad-1.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Linfoma de Hodgkin\\NPediátrico","guid":"wrguxAN1lO1UqpcaVLTokA","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"~10-15% de todos los LH → bimodal: pico 15-35a y >55a","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"En niños: 5-15% casos LH ocurre <15 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Sexo: PREDOMINIO MASCULINO en <10a (M:F ~4-5:1)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"En adolescentes: ratio se iguala","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"2do tumor más frecuente en adolescentes latinoamericanos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"7","parent":"1","text":"Asociación EBV: MAYOR en países en desarrollo (~80% vs 20% en desarrollados)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"8","parent":"0","text":"Clasificación WHO (2022)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"9","parent":"8","text":"CLÁSICO (~95%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"Esclerosis nodular (EN) → más frecuente en adolescentes y adultos jóvenes","guid":"","children":[{"id":"11","parent":"10","text":"Predomina en mediastino","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"10","text":"Células lacunares + colágeno","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"13","parent":"9","text":"Celularidad mixta (CM) → más frecuente en niños <10a","guid":"","children":[{"id":"14","parent":"13","text":"Asociación EBV más fuerte","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"13","text":"Estadios avanzados más comunes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"16","parent":"9","text":"Depleción linfocítica → raro, peor pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"17","parent":"9","text":"Rico en linfocitos → raro, buen pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"18","parent":"8","text":"PREDOMINIO LINFOCÍTICO NODULAR (PLN) (~5%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Células en palomita de maíz (LP cells)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"CD20+, CD15-, CD30-","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"Evolución indolente → manejo diferente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"18","text":"Mayor riesgo transformación a LDCGB tardío","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"23","parent":"0","text":"Biología y Célula de origen","guid":"","children":[{"id":"24","parent":"23","text":"Células Reed-Sternberg (CRS) → origen en linfocito B del centro germinal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"25","parent":"23","text":"CRS expresan: CD15+, CD30+ (AMBOS en cHL)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"23","text":"Microambiente tumoral: eosinófilos, neutrófilos, linfocitos T, histiocitos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"23","text":"Secreción citoquinas → síntomas B + inmunosupresión","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"23","text":"EBV → activa NF-κB → sobrevida celular tumoral","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"23","text":"Señalización JAK-STAT y PD-L1 → blancos terapéuticos actuales","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"Presentación Clínica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"ADENOPATÍA CERVICAL/SUPRACLAVICULAR → síntoma más común (>80%)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"Ganglios DUROS, NO dolorosos, progresivos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"33","parent":"30","text":"Masa mediastínica (30-40%) → puede causar SVC, tos, disnea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"30","text":"SÍNTOMAS B → factor pronóstico adverso","guid":"","children":[{"id":"35","parent":"34","text":"Fiebre >38C (sin foco) recurrente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"34","text":"Sudoración nocturna empapante","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"37","parent":"34","text":"Pérdida de peso >10% en 6 meses","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"38","parent":"30","text":"Prurito generalizado → no cuenta como síntoma B formal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"30","text":"Fatiga y anorexia","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"30","text":"Enfermedad extraganglionar: bazo, hígado, pulmón, hueso (estadios avanzados)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"0","text":"Diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"BIOPSIA EXCISIONAL ganglio → GOLD STANDARD (no solo aguja fina)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"43","parent":"42","text":"Histología + inmunohistoquímica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"44","parent":"42","text":"Marcadores cHL: CD15+, CD30+, CD20-, PAX5 débil","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"42","text":"Marcadores PLN: CD20+, CD79a+, BCL-6+, CD15-, CD30-","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"46","parent":"41","text":"Laboratorio inicial","guid":"","children":[{"id":"47","parent":"46","text":"Hemograma completo + diferencial","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"48","parent":"46","text":"VHS → valor pronóstico (>50mm/h = adverso)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"49","parent":"46","text":"LDH, beta-2-microglobulina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"46","text":"Ferritina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"46","text":"Albúmina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"46","text":"PCR, función hepática, renal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"53","parent":"46","text":"Serología EBV","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"54","parent":"41","text":"ESTADIFICACIÓN → PET-CT 18F-FDG → ESTÁNDAR ACTUAL","guid":"","children":[{"id":"55","parent":"54","text":"Sensibilidad superior a TC convencional","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"56","parent":"54","text":"Evalúa respuesta temprana (PET interino ciclo 2)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"57","parent":"54","text":"Criterios Deauville (escala 1-5)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"58","parent":"57","text":"Deauville 1-3 → respuesta metabólica completa (RMC)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"57","text":"Deauville 4-5 → respuesta insuficiente → escalar terapia","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"41","text":"Biopsia de médula ósea → solo si PET-CT no disponible o estadio IV clínico","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"0","text":"Estadificación (Lugano 2014)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"Estadio I → 1 región ganglionar o 1 sitio extralinfático (IE)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"Estadio II → 2 o más regiones mismo lado diafragma","guid":"","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"IIX → bulky (masa >1/3 diámetro transtorácico o >10cm)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"61","text":"Estadio III → regiones ambos lados diafragma","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"61","text":"Estadio IV → compromiso extralinfático difuso (hígado, pulmón, médula)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"61","text":"Sufijos: A = sin síntomas B; B = con síntomas B; E = extensión extralinfática","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"68","parent":"0","text":"Estratificación de Riesgo","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"BAJO RIESGO (LR)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"70","parent":"69","text":"Estadios IA, IB, IIA sin factores adversos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"69","text":"Sin masa bulky, sin síntomas B severos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"72","parent":"69","text":"EFS esperada >90%","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"73","parent":"68","text":"RIESGO INTERMEDIO (RI)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"74","parent":"73","text":"Estadios IIB, IIIA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"73","text":"o: IAX/IIX (con bulky)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"68","text":"ALTO RIESGO (AR)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"Estadios IIIB, IVA, IVB","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"PET-CT interino positivo (Deauville 4-5) tras 2 ciclos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"Masa bulky + síntomas B","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"80","parent":"0","text":"Tratamiento","guid":"","children":[{"id":"81","parent":"80","text":"PRINCIPIO: TRATAMIENTO ADAPTADO POR RESPUESTA (RAT)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"82","parent":"80","text":"Objetivo dual: curar con MÍNIMA toxicidad tardía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"80","text":"OS >90% con tratamiento moderno en niños","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"80","text":"Quimioterapia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"85","parent":"84","text":"OEPA → línea frontal (GPOH, COG europeo)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"86","parent":"85","text":"Oncocristina + Etopósido + Prednisona + Adriamicina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"85","text":"Ciclos 1-2 para TODOS los grupos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"85","text":"VENTAJA: evita bleomicina y dacarbazina → menor toxicidad tardía","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"84","text":"COPDac → continuación tras OEPA en RI/AR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"Ciclofosfamida + Oncocristina + Prednisona + Dacarbazina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"2 ciclos (RI) o 4 ciclos (AR)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"92","parent":"84","text":"ABVE-PC → protocolo COG (USA)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"93","parent":"92","text":"Adriamicina + Bleomicina + Vinblastina + Etopósido + Prednisona + Ciclofosfamida","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"94","parent":"92","text":"LR: 2-3 ciclos; AR: 5-6 ciclos","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"95","parent":"84","text":"ABVD → adultos → MENOS recomendado en niños <12a","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Bleomicina → toxicidad pulmonar en pulmón en desarrollo","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"97","parent":"80","text":"Radioterapia","guid":"","children":[{"id":"98","parent":"97","text":"INVOLVED SITE RT (ISRT) → estándar actual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"97","text":"Dosis: 15-25 Gy según respuesta PET interino y grupo riesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"100","parent":"97","text":"ELIMINAR RT si PET interino NEGATIVO → grupos LR y RI seleccionados","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Evita: cardiopatía, cáncer mama, hipotiroidismo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"102","parent":"97","text":"MANTENER RT en: bulky residual, PET positivo, AR","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"103","parent":"80","text":"Evaluación de Respuesta","guid":"","children":[{"id":"104","parent":"103","text":"PET-CT interino (tras ciclo 2) → PIEZA CLAVE del manejo moderno","guid":"","children":[{"id":"105","parent":"104","text":"PET negativo Deauville 1-3 → mantener esquema actual","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"106","parent":"104","text":"PET positivo Deauville 4-5 → escalar o añadir RT","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"107","parent":"103","text":"PET-CT final de quimioterapia → decisión definitiva sobre RT","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"108","parent":"0","text":"Recaída y Refractariedad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"109","parent":"108","text":"Recaída temprana (<12 meses) → PEOR pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"108","text":"Recaída tardía (>12 meses) → más sensible a 2ª línea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"108","text":"Quimioterapia de rescate","guid":"","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"ICE: Ifosfamida + Carboplatino + Etopósido","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"DHAP: Dexametasona + Citarabina + Cisplatino","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"114","parent":"108","text":"TRASPLANTE AUTÓLOGO → estándar en refractarios y recaída 1ª línea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"115","parent":"108","text":"BRENTUXIMAB VEDOTINA (BV) → anti-CD30 + agente citotóxico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"Aprobado pediátrico recaída/refractario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"Ensayos BV + AVD en frontline AR adolescentes (activos)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"118","parent":"108","text":"PEMBROLIZUMAB/NIVOLUMAB → anti-PD1","guid":"","children":[{"id":"119","parent":"118","text":"Alta actividad en cHL recaído/refractario","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"118","text":"PD-L1 sobreexpresado por amplificación 9q24.1","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"121","parent":"0","text":"Toxicidades Tardías","guid":"","children":[{"id":"122","parent":"121","text":"CARDIOTOXICIDAD → principal causa de mortalidad tardía","guid":"","children":[{"id":"123","parent":"122","text":"Antraciclinas → miocardiopatía dilatada dosis-dependiente","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"122","text":"RT mediastínica → pericarditis constrictiva, enfermedad coronaria precoz","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"122","text":"Monitoreo: ECO + ECG anual en sobrevivientes de por vida","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"126","parent":"121","text":"PULMONAR","guid":"","children":[{"id":"127","parent":"126","text":"Bleomicina → fibrosis pulmonar (EVITAR en niños <12a)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"128","parent":"126","text":"RT pulmonar → neumonitis + fibrosis","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"129","parent":"121","text":"ENDOCRINOPATÍAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"130","parent":"129","text":"Hipotiroidismo → 20-30% post-RT cervical","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"129","text":"Disfunción gonadal → ciclofosfamida + RT pélvica → criopreservación previa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"129","text":"Déficit GH si RT compromete columna vertebral alta","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"133","parent":"121","text":"SEGUNDAS NEOPLASIAS","guid":"","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"Cáncer de mama → principal en mujeres con RT torácica antes de 30a","guid":"","children":[{"id":"135","parent":"134","text":"Screening mamográfico desde 8-10 años post-RT","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"LMA → procarbazina + etopósido → MENOR riesgo con esquemas OEPA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"133","text":"Cáncer tiroides → post-RT cervical","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"0","text":"Pronóstico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"139","parent":"138","text":"GLOBAL: OS ~90-95% con tratamiento moderno en centros especializados","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"140","parent":"138","text":"EFS global: 80-90% según grupo de riesgo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"141","parent":"138","text":"BAJO RIESGO → OS >95%, EFS >90%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"142","parent":"138","text":"ALTO RIESGO → OS ~85-92%, EFS ~75-85%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"138","text":"PLN → OS >95% a 5 años → mejor pronóstico que cHL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"138","text":"Factores\\NPronósticos\\NADVERSOS\\N(factores clásicos)","guid":"d5JqjZoxmgWl-t9Mdee1Lg","children":[{"id":"145","parent":"144","text":"ESTADIO AVANZADO (III-IV) → principal","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"146","parent":"144","text":"SÍNTOMAS B → especialmente fiebre + pérdida de peso","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"147","parent":"144","text":"MASA BULKY (>10cm o >1/3 diámetro transtorácico)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"148","parent":"144","text":"VHS >50mm/h","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"144","text":"Albúmina <4 g/dL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"144","text":"Hemoglobina <10.5 g/dL","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"144","text":"Compromiso extraganglionar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"144","text":"Involucro de >3 regiones ganglionares","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"138","text":"IPS (International Prognostic Score)\\N— adultos; uso limitado en niños","guid":"H4jk7IzVO8aW8yZPFLQXLw","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"0-2 factores → pronóstico favorable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"3+ factores → pronóstico desfavorable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"Score pediátrico: adaptaciones en estudio (GPOH, COG)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"138","text":"PET-CT INTERINO →\\NPREDICTOR PRONÓSTICO\\NMÁS PODEROSO HOY","guid":"fuvsaZNbcTM-TcyEvUf6hg","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"PET negativo ciclo 2 (Deauville 1-3) → EFS ~90%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"157","text":"PET positivo ciclo 2 (Deauville 4-5) → EFS ~50-60% sin escalada","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"157","text":"RESPUESTA TEMPRANA RÁPIDA (RER) → factor favorable independiente","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"161","parent":"138","text":"Pronóstico según\\Nsubtipo histológico","guid":"R9YIaDehp4Jw0OAhiAlcGg","children":[{"id":"162","parent":"161","text":"Esclerosis nodular → pronóstico intermedio-favorable","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"161","text":"Celularidad mixta → pronóstico algo inferior, pero estadios más avanzados al debut","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"161","text":"Depleción linfocítica → PEOR pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"161","text":"Rico en linfocitos → MEJOR pronóstico (similar a PLN)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"166","parent":"138","text":"RECAÍDA →\\Npronóstico variable","guid":"4q7BTE9oC1aB8kZ0f9DtYg","children":[{"id":"167","parent":"166","text":"Recaída temprana (<12 meses) → OS ~50-60% a 5 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"166","text":"Recaída tardía (>12 meses) → OS ~70-80% con rescate","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"166","text":"Refractariedad primaria → peor escenario → trasplante + nuevos agentes","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"138","text":"Avances recientes en AR\\N(ensayos NEJM 2022-2024)","guid":"tLeaoVPoDznKLJEYwg6_TQ","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"BV + AVD (AHOD1331, NEJM 2022) → EFS 83% vs 73% ABVE-PC a 2 años en AR pediátrico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"172","parent":"171","text":"Con mayor toxicidad periférica (neuropatía)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"Nivolumab + AVD (SWOG S1826, NEJM 2024)\\N→ EFS superior a BV+AVD en adultos/AYA","guid":"kJTiA17e43iLW7oNjjBXAw","children":[{"id":"174","parent":"173","text":"Menor toxicidad nerviosa, sin bleomicina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"173","text":"Dato emergente en adolescentes → NO aprobado frontline pediátrico aún","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"176","parent":"138","text":"Mortalidad tardía en sobrevivientes\\N(>5 años post-tratamiento)","guid":"6zV9w4Cw4ffZbi-FXjtmwQ","children":[{"id":"177","parent":"176","text":"Principal causa: SEGUNDA NEOPLASIA (especialmente ca. mama)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"176","text":"Segunda causa: CARDIOPATÍA (post-RT mediastínica + antraciclinas)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"176","text":"Mortalidad tardía NO oncológica supera a recaída en sobrevivientes >10 años","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"176","text":"CURABILIDAD ALTA = responsabilidad de vigilar largo plazo","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"181","parent":"138","text":"Score Pronóstico PLN\\N(NEJM/JCO 2024)","guid":"wclx90AAUcHm7wAN4pWDYQ","children":[{"id":"182","parent":"181","text":"Factores adversos PLN: estadio avanzado, patrón B/C en IHQ, edad >18a","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"181","text":"Score internacional Global nLPHL → guía decisiones de manejo en PLN","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"184","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clínicas","guid":"","children":[{"id":"185","parent":"184","text":"GANGLIOS DUROS NO DOLOROSOS en adolescente → pensar LH hasta descartar","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"184","text":"BIOPSIA EXCISIONAL obligatoria → aguja fina INSUFICIENTE para diagnóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"184","text":"PLN se maneja distinto → no RT extensa, vigilancia en estadios IA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"184","text":"PET-CT interino negativo → permite OMITIR RT → reduce toxicidad tardía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"184","text":"FIEBRE + PÉRDIDA DE PESO son los síntomas B de mayor impacto pronóstico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"184","text":"EBV positivo → celularidad mixta, países en desarrollo, niños <10a","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"184","text":"BLEOMICINA → evitar en niños → esquemas OEPA/COPDac la excluyen","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"184","text":"Brentuximab vedotina + AVD → dato emergente en adolescentes AR frontline","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"184","text":"Vigilancia cardiovascular POST-RT mediastínica → TODA LA VIDA","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"194","parent":"184","text":"OS >90% = curación esperable → priorizar CALIDAD DE VIDA A LARGO PLAZO","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"195","parent":"0","text":"VER TAMBIÉN","guid":"","children":[{"id":"196","parent":"195","text":"→ Linfoma No-Hodgkin (Oncología)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"195","text":"→ Leucemia Mieloide Aguda (Hematología)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"1. Belsky JA, Hochberg J, Giulino-Roth L. Diagnosis and management of Hodgkin lymphoma in children, adolescents, and young adults. Best Pract Res Clin Haematol. 2023;36(1):101445.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"2. Rossi C, et al. Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma: The LYSA pragmatic guidelines. Eur J Cancer. 2024;213:115073.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"198","text":"3. Parambil BC, et al. Clinical profile and outcome of classical Hodgkin lymphoma treated with a risk-adapted approach. Pediatr Blood Cancer. 2020;67(2):e28058.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"198","text":"4. Ali N, et al. Outcome and prognostic factors of pediatric patients with Hodgkin lymphoma. J Egypt Natl Canc Inst. 2023;35(1):29.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"203","parent":"198","text":"5. Castellino SM, et al. Brentuximab Vedotin with Chemotherapy in Pediatric High-Risk Hodgkin Lymphoma. N Engl J Med. 2022;387(18):1649-60. DOI: 10.1056/NEJMoa2206660","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"204","parent":"198","text":"6. Evens AM, et al. Nivolumab + AVD in Advanced-Stage Classic Hodgkin Lymphoma. N Engl J Med. 2024. DOI: 10.1056/NEJMoa2405888","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"198","text":"7. Spinner MA, et al. International Prognostic Score for Nodular Lymphocyte-Predominant Hodgkin Lymphoma. J Clin Oncol. 2024. DOI: 10.1200/JCO.23.01655","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},"node_count":205,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/General","filename":"LH Pediatrico iPad-1","id":"map_797","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"LH Pediatrico iPad-1"}